fig.ts`**\n\n37 lines providing schema handling:\n- `DEFAULT_DB_SCHEMA = \"public\"`\n- `loadDbSchemaFromEnv()` — reads DB_SCHEMA env var, defaults to \"public\"\n- `applyDbSchemaToUrl()` — appends `-csearch_path=<schema>` to URL search params if non-default\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Migration Runner: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`**\n\n158 lines implementing idempotent SQL migration system:\n- Reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` directory in lexicographic order\n- Creates `_migrations` table to track applied versions\n- `runMigrations()` applies pending migrations in transactions\n- `showStatus()` displays applied vs pending migrations\n- CLI: `tsx src/migrate.ts` to run, `tsx src/migrate.ts status` to check\n- Schema support via `DB_SCHEMA` environment variable\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Migrations Directory Listing**\n\nAll files in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/`:\n\n| File | Size | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `001_init.sql` | 1.2 KB | Create `rounds`, `operator_events` tables + indexes |\n| `002_auth_sessions.sql` | 839 B | Auth session table (for JWT/challenge system) |\n| `003_tier_to_amount.sql` | 256 B | Replace tier field with amount_lamports |\n| `004_match_id_index.sql` | 149 B | Add index on match_id for deep-link lookups |\n| `005_closecall_rounds.sql` | 1.7 KB | Create `closecall_rounds` table (pari-mutuel, oracle) |\n| `006_closecall_candles.sql` | 869 B | Create `closecall_candles` table (cached Pyth prices) |\n| `007_round_entries.sql` | 310 B | Add JSONB entries column to rounds table |\n\n**Total migrations applied: 7**\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Most Recent Migration: `007_round_entries.sql`**\n\n```sql\n-- 007_round_entries.sql — Add entries JSONB column to rounds table.\n--\n-- Stores player entries at settlement time for direct access without\n-- needing to read from operator_events. Nullable for backward compat\n-- with existing rows.\n\nALTER TABLE rounds ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS entries JSONB DEFAULT NULL;\n```\n\nThis migration adds a `entries` JSONB column to the `rounds` table to store player entries (array of `{player, amountLamports}` objects) at settlement time, avoiding the need to query `operator_events` for history reconstruction.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Route Directory Structure: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/`**\n\nSix route files:\n\n| File | Size | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `auth.ts` | 8.5 KB | Challenge-response JWT, login/logout, session management |\n| `closecall.ts` | 12.8 KB | Close Call round operations (join, settle, history, current round) |\n| `create.ts` | 7.3 KB | Coinflip/Lord match creation, fairness data retrieval |\n| `health.ts` | 1.8 KB | Health check endpoint |\n| `lord-create.ts` | 8.6 KB | Lord of RNGs-specific match creation |\n| `rounds.ts` | 7.4 KB | Round query endpoints (get by matchId, by PDA, recent history) |\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Next Available Migration Number**\n\n**`008`** — The next migration should be named `008_<description>.sql`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Database Schema Summary**\n\n**tables:**\n- `rounds` — Commit-reveal game rounds (Coinflip, Lord of RNGs)\n  - Columns: pda (PK), game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, side, match_id, phase, target_slot, settle_tx, settle_attempts, result_hash, result_side, winner, entries (JSONB), created_at, updated_at\n  - Indexes: phase, creator, match_id\n\n- `operator_events` — Audit log for settlement/lifecycle events\n  - Columns: id (PK), pda, event_type, payload (JSONB), created_at\n  - Indexes: (pda, created_at), (event_type, created_at)\n\n- `closecall_rounds` — Oracle-based pari-mutuel rounds\n  - Columns: round_id (PK), pda (UNIQUE), server_key, phase, open_price, open_price_expo, close_price, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, total_fee, green_entries (JSONB), red_entries (JSONB), settle_tx, created_at, settled_at\n  - Indexes: phase, (settled_at DESC)\n\n- `